The decrease in photocurrent when the UV light was turned off depends on the rate at which oxygen molecules are absorbed onto the surface of ZnO nanostructures. The decrease in photocurrent of these nanostructured films was fitted with first order exponential decay:1I(t)=Id+(Ip−Id)exp[−(t/τ)]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
